FTimeField.picker({
  FTimeFieldControl control,
  FPopoverControl popoverControl,

  DateFormat? format,
  TextAlign textAlign,
  TextAlignVertical? textAlignVertical,
  TextDirection? textDirection,
  bool expands,
  MouseCursor mouseCursor,
  bool canRequestFocus,
  String? hint,
  bool autofocus,
  FocusNode? focusNode,
  Alignment anchor,
  Alignment fieldAnchor,
  FPortalConstraints constraints,
  FPortalSpacing spacing,
  FPortalOverflow overflow,
  Offset offset,
  FPopoverHideRegion hideRegion,
  Object? groupId,
  void Function()? onTapHide,
  int hourInterval,
  int minuteInterval,
  Widget Function(BuildContext, FTimeFieldStyle, Set<WidgetState>, Widget)
  builder,
  Widget Function(BuildContext, FTimeFieldStyle, Set<WidgetState>)?
  prefixBuilder,
  Widget Function(BuildContext, FTimeFieldStyle, Set<WidgetState>)?
  suffixBuilder,
  Widget? label,
  Widget? description,
  bool enabled,
  void Function(FTime?)? onSaved,
  void Function()? onReset,
  AutovalidateMode autovalidateMode,
  String? forceErrorText,
  Widget Function(BuildContext, String) errorBuilder,
  Key? key,
})

Core.name: Core

Control.name: `.managed()` with internal controller

control: .managed(
    initial: const FTime(9, 30),
    validator: (time) => null,

  ),

Control.name: `.managed()` with external controller
Control.description: Uses an external controller for time field management.

Control.name: `.lifted()`
Control.description: Externally controls the time field value.
Control.text:
control: .lifted(
    time: const FTime(9, 30),
    onChange: (time) {},
    duration: const Duration(milliseconds: 300),
    curve: Curves.easeOutCubic,
  ),

    onChange: (shown) {},
